03:02.184 --> 03:04.418
How is it sexist?

03:04.420 --> 03:08.339
My character wields a
battle axe as well as any man.

03:09.475 --> 03:11.392
Not to mention she
has mammary glands

03:11.394 --> 03:13.094
that could
nurse a family of 30.

03:14.396 --> 03:19.650
And have enough milk left over
to open a Baskin Robbins.

03:19.652 --> 03:23.488
Mother, warrior-princess,
franchise owner--

03:23.490 --> 03:26.858
I hear glass ceilings
shattering all over town.

03:26.860 --> 03:28.609
Sheldon,
you're always saying

03:28.611 --> 03:30.495
how much smarter
you are than me.

03:30.497 --> 03:32.363
Spend five seconds
and come up with one idea

03:32.365 --> 03:34.248
on how to get more women
into science.

03:36.001 --> 03:39.453
All your ideas address the issue
at a university level.

03:39.455 --> 03:40.505
By then it's too late.

03:40.507 --> 03:42.723
You need to
design an outreach program

03:42.725 --> 03:44.425
that targets girls
at the middle school level

03:44.427 --> 03:46.294
and sets them on an
academic track

03:46.296 --> 03:47.762
towards the hard sciences.

03:47.764 --> 03:49.497
That's actually good.

03:49.499 --> 03:51.883
Why didn't I
think of that?

03:51.885 --> 03:54.051
Some people are otters,
some people are rocks.

03:57.940 --> 03:59.440
I wonder if there's a way

03:59.442 --> 04:01.842
we could give the idea
a trial run.

04:01.844 --> 04:05.363
Maybe I could call my old
middle school,

04:05.365 --> 04:08.182
see if we can talk to some of
the female students.

04:08.184 --> 04:09.350
That's great--
try to set up something

04:09.352 --> 04:10.985
for the three of us
to go over there.

04:10.987 --> 04:12.203
Oh, hold on.

04:12.205 --> 04:14.005
While I'm comfortable speaking
about science,

04:14.007 --> 04:16.991
I'm not sure I know how to spark
the interest of schoolchildren.

04:16.993 --> 04:19.459
Better Google it.

04:19.462 --> 04:21.512
What exactly are you looking up?

04:21.514 --> 04:25.750
"How do I get
12-year-old girls excited."

04:25.752 --> 04:27.618
No!
No!

04:32.457 --> 04:35.142
Thanks again for letting
me crash "girls' night."

04:35.144 --> 04:36.177
Are you kidding?

04:36.179 --> 04:38.212
You brought fancy
wine and made fondue.

04:38.214 --> 04:40.598
I've slept
with guys for less.

04:45.437 --> 04:47.355
It's a joke.

04:47.357 --> 04:49.556
Based on real events.

04:49.558 --> 04:52.827
Anyway,
I was hoping I could, uh,

04:52.829 --> 04:53.945
pick your brains a little.

04:53.947 --> 04:55.663
I'm supposed to take
Lucy out Friday

04:55.665 --> 04:57.448
and I need a killer first date.

04:57.450 --> 05:00.785
Well, evolutionary biology
says that women are attracted

05:00.787 --> 05:03.254
to a man who is steady
in the face of danger,

05:03.256 --> 05:05.873
so I recommend an
unsafe environment.

05:06.925 --> 05:10.845
Seedy bar on the wrong
side of the tracks...

05:10.847 --> 05:14.248
picnic near
a lunatic asylum...

05:14.250 --> 05:17.351
a wine tasting on Skid Row.

05:18.437 --> 05:21.806
Eh, Lucy has some,
uh, social anxiety issues.

05:21.808 --> 05:23.641
Maybe we could start
with something simpler.

05:23.643 --> 05:26.060
Why don't you take
her to Disneyland?

05:26.062 --> 05:27.528
You go on Space Mountain,

05:27.530 --> 05:29.413
you're in the dark,
she's holding onto you.

05:29.415 --> 05:30.531
Yeah, but you
just have to remember,

05:30.533 --> 05:31.983
that ride is
shorter than you think

05:31.985 --> 05:33.934
and they take a
picture of you at the end,

05:33.936 --> 05:36.070
so make sure
you got your clothes back on.

05:38.407 --> 05:41.292
It's a joke.

05:41.294 --> 05:43.244
Based on real events.

05:43.246 --> 05:44.278
Mm, Disneyland?

05:44.280 --> 05:45.663
I don't know.

05:45.665 --> 05:47.748
With all the crowds and the
weird characters walking around,

05:47.750 --> 05:49.750
just reminds me
too much of India.

05:51.720 --> 05:53.587
I haven't been to Disneyland
since I was a kid.

05:53.589 --> 05:54.922
We should
definitely go one weekend.

05:54.924 --> 05:56.307
Weekends are too crowded.

05:56.309 --> 05:58.009
So, blow off work,
go on a weekday.

05:58.011 --> 05:59.644
Hooky?

05:59.646 --> 06:01.696
I've never
played hooky in my life.

06:01.698 --> 06:03.581
My mom said
that's how girls end up

06:03.583 --> 06:06.183
addicted to
reefer and jazz music.

06:07.619 --> 06:10.471
It's more like how girls end up
at a Best Western hotel

06:10.473 --> 06:12.907
with a 34-year-old guy
named Luther.

06:15.027 --> 06:16.027
Joke?

06:16.029 --> 06:18.579
I can laugh about it now.

06:21.667 --> 06:22.867
So, what do you say?

06:22.869 --> 06:24.535
This Friday we ditch work
and go to Disneyland?

06:24.537 --> 06:25.569
I'm in.

06:25.571 --> 06:27.204
Me, too.

06:27.206 --> 06:28.372
Excuse me,

06:28.374 --> 06:30.958
I thought we were trying to
solve my problem?

06:30.960 --> 06:32.510
Oh, yeah, right.

06:32.512 --> 06:33.794
Wait, what was your problem
again?

06:33.796 --> 06:37.164
I am a man
who can't talk to women,

06:37.166 --> 06:39.517
trying to figure out how to go
on a romantic date

06:39.519 --> 06:41.552
with a girl who suffers
from such crippling

06:41.554 --> 06:44.772
social anxiety she can't be
around other people.

06:44.774 --> 06:47.425
Yeah, that's a toughie.

06:48.627 --> 06:50.761
Let's think.

06:50.763 --> 06:51.929
Hmm.

06:57.135 --> 07:01.572
We doing just Disney
or California Adventure, too?

07:02.708 --> 07:04.709
It's nice
of your old school

07:04.711 --> 07:07.745
to let us try out our science
talk on some female students.

07:07.747 --> 07:08.963
Well, they're
actually pretty excited.

07:08.965 --> 07:11.148
I'm their
most famous alum.

07:11.150 --> 07:12.483
If you don't
count the serial killer

07:12.485 --> 07:14.201
who ate all
those prostitutes.

07:16.338 --> 07:17.755
This must feel
pretty good for you,

07:17.757 --> 07:20.141
coming back to your
alma mater as an astronaut.

07:20.143 --> 07:25.012
Yeah, last time I was here, I
was just a scrawny little nerd.

07:25.014 --> 07:28.715
And now
you're also an astronaut.

07:28.717 --> 07:29.900
So many memories.

07:29.902 --> 07:32.353
I mean, how many
times in these hallways

07:32.355 --> 07:36.407
was I tripped,
punched and spit on?

07:36.409 --> 07:38.559
Oh, look,
here's my old locker.

07:38.561 --> 07:41.212
I have a
masters in engineering

07:41.214 --> 07:44.749
and I still can't figure out
how Scott Kapinski

07:44.751 --> 07:46.917
got me and my briefcase
to fit in there.

07:50.622 --> 07:51.839
Hey.

07:51.841 --> 07:53.907
What?

07:53.909 --> 07:55.543
Nothing.

07:57.963 --> 08:00.214
Smart. We don't
want any problems.

08:02.434 --> 08:04.718
I can't believe I ditched work
for Disneyland.

08:04.720 --> 08:06.470
What did you
tell your boss?

08:06.472 --> 08:08.889
Oh, I was very clever,
I did it in stages.

08:08.891 --> 08:10.524
At 7:00 last night,

08:10.526 --> 08:12.276
I called about
a problem at the lab

08:12.278 --> 08:14.695
and casually mentioned
I was going out for seafood.

08:14.697 --> 08:16.147
At 9:30,

08:16.149 --> 08:19.733
I called and told him that
one of my scallops tasted weird.

08:19.735 --> 08:21.452
At 11:30, I called and said

08:21.454 --> 08:23.404
I was
throwing up like a fire hose.

08:25.073 --> 08:29.276
At 12:45, I called and made
nothing but dry heaving sounds,

08:29.278 --> 08:31.579
and now I'm
going to Disneyland.

08:33.248 --> 08:35.166
Penny, what did you say?

08:35.168 --> 08:36.467
I work at the
Cheesecake Factory,

08:36.469 --> 08:38.251
I said "bye."

08:39.721 --> 08:41.755
So, what are we
gonna do first?

08:41.756 --> 08:42.972
I don't know
about you guys,

08:42.975 --> 08:44.258
but I'm gonna make
a beeline for the place

08:44.260 --> 08:45.643
that gives you
a princess makeover.

08:45.645 --> 08:47.261
Ooh, that sounds like fun.

08:47.263 --> 08:48.762
You're
kidding, right?

08:48.764 --> 08:51.348
We're not just gonna get drunk
and go on rides?

08:51.350 --> 08:54.401
Come on, do it with us.

08:54.403 --> 08:56.187
All right, whatever.

08:56.189 --> 08:57.404
How does it work?

08:57.406 --> 08:58.639
Okay, so,
you pick your princess--

08:58.641 --> 09:00.691
Sleeping Beauty, Snow White
Cinderella--

09:00.693 --> 09:03.027
they give you
hair, makeup, the works.

09:03.029 --> 09:06.313
Guess it would be fun
to be Cinderella.

09:06.315 --> 09:07.865
Oh, I want to be Cinderella, too.
Yeah.

09:09.035 --> 09:11.085
We can't all be Cinderella.

09:14.122 --> 09:15.422
Then how do we decide?

09:15.424 --> 09:16.540
Well, it's simple.

09:16.542 --> 09:17.824
This was my idea.

09:17.826 --> 09:18.843
I'm driving.

09:18.845 --> 09:19.760
I'm Cinderella.

09:19.762 --> 09:21.328
You bitches
got a problem with that,

09:21.330 --> 09:23.347
we could stop the car right now.

